m/img/07e7/04/1d/1109962627_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_a8406c68c177d3f91428453111359fca.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1d/1109962627_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_0969ac8f7429c44b6dea6c5ce5069807.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/1d/1109962627_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_18bb0a36ef8c57ec657ecab39f193b40.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Ohad Zwigenberg </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据特拉维夫（人造卫星）网报道：周六晚上，数千名以色列人在特拉维夫集会，抗议总理本雅明内塔尼亚胡改革司法机构的计划，这已成为例行公事。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这是第 20 次示威，反对许多以色列人认为企图削弱最高法院权力的示威。自今年年初以来，集会几乎每周都在持续。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">组织者将出席人数定为 135,000 人，低于前几周估计的约 200,000 人。更多示威活动发生在耶路撒冷、海法、阿什杜德、荷兹利亚和数十个较小的城镇。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">周六晚上的集会还试图让人们关注内塔尼亚胡的 2023-2024 年预算提案，该提案已指定 137 亿谢克尔（38 亿美元）用于资助他的极端正统派和亲定居者联盟伙伴的倡议。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 23:31:06 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/thousands-protest-netanyahus-judicial-reform-in-tel-aviv-1110492481.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/thousands-protest-netanyahus-judicial-reform-in-tel-aviv-1110492481.html<category>世界</category><category>本杰明·内塔尼亚胡</category><category>特拉维夫</category><category>反对</category><category>政治抗议</category><category>司法改革</category><category>以色列</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Sudanese Rivals Agree Humanitarian Ceasefire From Saturday - Reports]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110492361" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/0f/1109561263_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_3f47ce347cf340db048b9f2ecd5fec7c.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1109561095" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/sudanese-rivals-agree-humanitarian-ceasefire-from-saturday---reports-1110492361.html?share-img=1109561095"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Marwan Ali</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2023 年 4 月 15 日，星期六，烟雾从苏丹喀土穆的一个街区升起。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Smoke is seen rising from a neighborhood in Khartoum, Sudan, Saturday, April 15, 2023. - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="2023 年 4 月 15 日，星期六，烟雾从苏丹喀土穆的一个街区升起。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/0f/1109561263_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_0aea1ba99dabb7d7b150e09a751fb9b4.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/0f/1109561263_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_5f70b6048bc6994fec4aab9c94f58bcc.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/0f/1109561263_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_b98688e142ba57cb6990bfe67e91ebae.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/0f/1109561263_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_0aea1ba99dabb7d7b150e09a751fb9b4.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Marwan Ali </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据多哈（人造卫星）网报道：据卡塔尔媒体报道，苏丹冲突各方已同意为期一周的停火协议，将从周六开始允许人道主义人员进入冲突地区。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据半岛电视台新闻网报道，苏丹武装部队和叛军准军事快速支援部队的谈判代表在沙特吉达市达成了协议。该协议可以延长。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “冲突各方承诺开放人道主义‘走廊’，以促进向平民提供人道主义援助。他们重申承诺将部队尽可能从医院和医疗机构撤出，”一位知情人士在事后告诉人造卫星网。在吉达的会谈结束了。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">当天早些时候，美国国务卿安东尼·布林肯致电苏丹武装部队总司令阿卜杜勒·法塔赫·布尔汉，讨论吉达会谈的进展情况。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “国务卿敦促灵活性和领导力。国务卿再次谴责双方的暴力行为……强调在吉达达成的协议将允许提供人道主义援助和基本服务，”国务院发言人马修米勒说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110492361" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/sudanese-rivals-agree-humanitarian-ceasefire-from-saturday---reports-1110492361.html?share-block=1110492364" data-title="&quot;The Secretary urged flexibility and leadership. The Secretary again condemned the violence by both parties… underscoring that agreement in Jeddah would allow the provision of humanitarian assistance and essential services,&quot; State Department spokesperson Matthew Miller said. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 4月15日，苏丹正规军与快速支援部队爆发激烈冲突，震中位于喀土穆。政府军指责 RSF 叛变并对他们的基地发动空袭。此后，双方在全国范围内实施了多次临时停火，但冲突尚未平息。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据世界卫生组织估计，自 4 月中旬以来，约有 705 人在战斗中丧生，至少有 5,287 人受伤。双方都对随之而来的人道主义危机负责，粮食、水和燃料严重短缺，电力供应有限。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 23:10:09 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/sudanese-rivals-agree-humanitarian-ceasefire-from-saturday---reports-1110492361.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/sudanese-rivals-agree-humanitarian-ceasefire-from-saturday---reports-1110492361.html<category>军队</category><category>苏丹</category><category>快速支援部队 (RSF)</category><category>世界卫生组织 (WHO)</category><category>吉达</category><category>安东尼布林肯</category><category>苏丹军队</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[US to Supply Ukraine With 'Everything They Need' Ahead of Offensive, White House Official Says]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110492238" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/09/1110211152_0:0:2653:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_a7c346bec9218c21572787a177f223f3.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110211134" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/us-to-supply-ukraine-with-everything-they-need-ahead-of-offensive-white-house-official-says-1110492238.html?share-img=1110211134"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / DANIEL SLIM</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">白宫于 2022 年 5 月 19 日在华盛顿特区亮相</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="The White House is seen on May 19, 2022 in Washington, DC - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="白宫于 2022 年 5 月 19 日在华盛顿特区亮相" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/09/1110211152_0:278:2653:1770_1920x0_80_0_0_fdde1c596abf5ab7924a76d780a09d85.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/09/1110211152_0:278:2653:1770_640x0_80_0_0_4cb5d379a141f61dfd005978d0a72360.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/09/1110211152_0:278:2653:1770_1280x0_80_0_0_e1d307a4dd64923005823e821e76e96d.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/09/1110211152_0:278:2653:1770_1920x0_80_0_0_fdde1c596abf5ab7924a76d780a09d85.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / 丹尼尔斯利姆</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：一名白宫高级官员周六表示，美国希望向乌克兰提供它所需的一切，以便在俄罗斯控制的领土前成功发动进攻。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">拜登政府官员在一次简报会上说：“我们希望确保乌克兰拥有他们决定进攻时取得成功所需的一切。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他告诉记者，预计在不久的将来，通过总统缩编授权 (PDA)，美国武器库存将进一步缩减。美国将从其军火库中撤出并提供给乌克兰的武器包括大炮、小型武器、弹药、爆破设备以及可能更多的 HIMARS 弹药。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “你应该期待在不久的将来看到掌上电脑……过去几周我们一直在为乌克兰提供的各种能力，因为他们一直在为天气好转和进攻的可能性做准备在接下来的几周和几个月里，他们自己，”他说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110492238" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/us-to-supply-ukraine-with-everything-they-need-ahead-of-offensive-white-house-official-says-1110492238.html?share-block=1110492241" data-title="&quot;You should expect to see in the near future of PDAs… the kinds of capabilities that we have been providing Ukraine over these last several weeks, as they've been preparing for the weather to get better and for the possibility of going on the offense on their own in the weeks and months ahead,&quot; he said. "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Politico 本周报道称，美国总统乔·拜登周日在日本七国集团峰会期间与乌克兰的沃洛德米尔·泽伦斯基会面后，将承诺向乌克兰提供额外的 3.75 亿美元军事援助。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 22:03:39 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/us-to-supply-ukraine-with-everything-they-need-ahead-of-offensive-white-house-official-says-1110492238.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/us-to-supply-ukraine-with-everything-they-need-ahead-of-offensive-white-house-official-says-1110492238.html<category>俄罗斯在乌克兰的特别行动</category><category>美国为乌克兰提供武器</category><category>美乌关系</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>G7峰会</category><category>军队</category><category>海玛斯</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia Opens Criminal Probe Into Kiev-Instigated Quran Burning]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110492121" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103189/89/1031898913_0:0:4455:2970_1440x900_80_0_1_cee1e3a531a5e81a3b0aca6e0014619c.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1031898912" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/russia-opens-criminal-probe-into-kiev-instigated-quran-burning-1110492121.html?share-img=1031898912"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Matt Rourke</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2015 年 11 月 18 日星期三，叙利亚难民打开她的《古兰经》，由于害怕生活在叙利亚的家人遭到报复，同意在匿名的情况下拍照</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Syrian refugee, who agreed to be photograph on condition of anonymity because of fear of retaliation against family living in Syria, opens her Quran, Wednesday, Nov. 18, 2015 - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="2015 年 11 月 18 日，星期三，叙利亚难民打开她的古兰经，由于害怕生活在叙利亚的家人遭到报复，同意在匿名的情况下拍照" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103189/89/1031898913_0:233:4455:2739_1920x0_80_0_0_69909e453dc7a63ba03f25e96ec699a6.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103189/89/1031898913_0:233:4455:2739_640x0_80_0_0_920738b5c75e998d9e1328a3e899c465.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103189/89/1031898913_0:233:4455:2739_1280x0_80_0_0_40f4979a6372778d36c4b044ec76850f.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/103189/89/1031898913_0:233:4455:2739_1920x0_80_0_0_69909e453dc7a63ba03f25e96ec699a6.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © AP Photo / 马特·洛克</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：俄罗斯主要调查机构周六宣布，对最近在伏尔加格勒焚烧穆斯林圣书《古兰经》的副本进行刑事调查，怀疑是在乌克兰策划的。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">调查委员会告诉卫星通讯社：“当地居民 Nikita Zhuravel 因涉嫌触犯俄罗斯刑法第 148 条第 2 款的罪行而被捕。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在一名男子在伏尔加格勒一座清真寺前焚烧古兰经的视频被上传到网上后，俄罗斯调查人员展开了搜捕行动。如果罪名成立，朱拉维尔将面临最高三年的监禁，罪名是冒犯宗教感情。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">该委员会告诉人造卫星，嫌疑人已经承认从乌克兰特工那里收到了 10,000 卢布（125 美元）作为布置和拍摄古兰经焚烧的奖励。他还说他为乌克兰人制作了俄罗斯军事基地的视频。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110492121" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/russia-opens-criminal-probe-into-kiev-instigated-quran-burning-1110492121.html?share-block=1110492124" data-title="The committee told Sputnik that the suspect had confessed to receiving 10,000 rubles ($125) from Ukrainian agents as a reward for staging and filming the Quran burning. He also said he had made videos of Russian military sites for Ukrainians."></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 21:02:02 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/russia-opens-criminal-probe-into-kiev-instigated-quran-burning-1110492121.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/russia-opens-criminal-probe-into-kiev-instigated-quran-burning-1110492121.html<category>俄罗斯</category><category>调查</category><category>俄罗斯调查委员会</category><category>古兰经</category><category>伊斯兰教</category><category>伏尔加格勒</category><category>乌克兰危机</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Durham Report: Is Reckoning Coming for Clintons and Bidens?]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110490817" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107851/17/1078511724_0:0:3071:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_780e39bf99587cd9a0dca8494de4280d.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1078511722" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/durham-report-is-reckoning-coming-for-clintons-and-bidens-1110490817.html?share-img=1078511722"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Evan Vucci</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">副总统乔·拜登（左）与前国务卿希拉里·克林顿在 12 月 8 日星期四于国会山举行的参议院少数党领袖哈里·里德肖像揭幕仪式上与前国务卿希拉里·克林顿一起大笑。 2016 年，华盛顿。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Vice President Joe Biden, left, laughs with former Secretary of State Hillary Clinton during a ceremony to unveil a portrait of Senate Minority Leader Harry Reid, D-Nev., on Capitol Hill, Thursday, Dec. 8, 2016, in Washington. - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="2016 年 12 月 8 日星期四，在华盛顿举行的参议院少数党领袖哈里·里德肖像揭幕仪式上，副总统乔·拜登（左）与前国务卿希拉里·克林顿一起大笑。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107851/17/1078511724_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_3033426f462bb53b03d71625ff188443.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107851/17/1078511724_0:161:3071:1888_640x0_80_0_0_af6b1702ac8706bd2e380fea981c7cac.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107851/17/1078511724_0:161:3071:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_d98d07670f5f22582c75c607860c8e28.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/107851/17/1078511724_0:161:3071:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_3033426f462bb53b03d71625ff188443.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Evan Vucci </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">叶卡捷琳娜布林诺娃</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_ekaterina_blinova/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:e.blinova@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">特别顾问约翰达勒姆关于特朗普 - 俄罗斯调查的报告产生了意想不到的副作用：众议院共和党立法者现在呼吁联邦调查局重新开始对克林顿基金会的调查。 Sputnik 与华尔街分析师 Charles Ortel 讨论了这一发展。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “人们希望约翰·达勒姆分享的内容绰绰有余，以促使人们更严格地了解克林顿基金会丑闻的广泛范围，这些丑闻首先由调查记者报道，包括约翰·所罗门和彼得·施韦泽，他们实际上应该获得普利策奖，”查尔斯·奥特尔说，他是几年来一直在对克林顿夫妇的慈善网络进行私人调查。 “ <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230216/why-elon-musk-would-have-made-great-special-counsel--independent-journos-do-better-job-than-doj-1107514193.html" target="_blank">主流媒体‘调查员’</a>对试图理解为什么奥巴马政府中有如此多的人参与了令人发指的行为，而这些行为随后被高层政府官员及其在许多官僚机构的同谋所掩盖，对此表现出不小的兴趣。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">尽管<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230516/durham-report-what-is-known-so-far-1110402005.html" target="_blank">约翰·达勒姆 (John Durham) 被指派调查</a>联邦调查局 (FBI) 交叉火力飓风调查的起源，目的是挖掘唐纳德·特朗普竞选活动涉嫌与俄罗斯的关系，但特别检察官也揭示了强大的民主党参与者，包括前总统候选人希拉里·克林顿 (Hillary Clinton) <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230209/whos-jake-sullivan-the-man-who-reportedly-assembled-dream-team-to-destroy-nord-stream-1107273707.html" target="_blank">及其随行人员</a>.达勒姆冗长的法庭动议暴露了克林顿竞选团队在兜售将他与俄罗斯阿尔法银行和克里姆林宫联系起来的反特朗普恶作剧中的作用。早在 2018 年，特别顾问罗伯特·穆勒 (Robert Mueller) 就得出结论，认为特朗普与俄罗斯的故事没有证据依据。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">此外，达勒姆提请注意这样一个事实，即联邦调查局<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230515/us-special-counsel-probe-finds-fbis-handling-of-trump-russia-probe-seriously-deficient-1110387179.html" target="_blank">在以可疑借口匆忙调查特朗普的</a>同时，对唐纳德的总统竞争对手希拉里克林顿进行了至少四次调查。 2016 年初，联邦调查局在阿肯色州、纽约和哥伦比亚特区的外地办事处启动了上述三项针对克林顿基金会的“可能犯罪活动”的调查。另一项调查早在 2014 年就开始了，原因是有人声称外国政府试图向克林顿夫妇的慈善机构非法捐款，以讨好希拉里担任国务卿期间的好感。令人费解的是，该局的所有四项调查都在 2016 年选举之前被关闭。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">美国联邦机构此前多次未能调查克林顿慈善机构</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">Ortel 强调说，克林顿基金会很早就进入了美国联邦当局的视线。尽管如此，据他说，每次调查人员都未能完成他们的调查并发现明显的不一致和明显的欺诈行为。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “公开的记录显示，从 2001 年 2 月到 2005 年初，詹姆斯·康梅、罗伯特·穆勒、美国国税局和其他人首先调查了最初的克林顿基金会，调查人员‘遗漏’了明显的欺诈行为。起初，这令人惊讶，因为调查人员应该能够看到，在 2001 年至 2004 年的关键时期，克林顿基金会从未对财务报表进行必要的审计，当时阿肯色州小石城总统中心得到资助和建设，”这位华尔街分析师说。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110490817" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/durham-report-is-reckoning-coming-for-clintons-and-bidens-1110490817.html?share-block=1110491947" data-title="&quot;Publicly available records show that the original Clinton Foundation was first investigated by James Comey, Robert Mueller, the IRS, and others from February 2001 through early 2005 and that the investigators 'missed' obvious frauds. This is surprising, at first, in that investigators should have been able to see that the Clinton Foundation never produced required audits of financial statements in the crucial period from 2001 through 2004, when the Little Rock, Arkansas Presidential Center was financed and constructed,&quot; said the Wall Street analyst."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “公共记录还显示，克林顿基金会从未在 1997 年 10 月 23 日至 1997 年 12 月 31 日这一关键的‘短期’期间提交必要的国税局报告，当时本应为克林顿第二届就职委员会筹集的剩余资金被捐赠给克林顿基金会。基金会。在 2005 年 4 月 25 日之后，我的评估是威廉·克林顿总统基金会不再是一种可行的免税实体形式，被称为“公共慈善机构”，因为它未能完全修改其公司章程和章程，并且此外，在比尔·克林顿的直接监督下，最初的克林顿基金会于 2001 年夏天开始筹集资金并从事从未被美国国税局有效授权为免税的活动，当时它使用纽约的办事处城市没有遵守严格的州和城市慈善法，”Ortel 继续说道。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据这位华尔街分析师的说法，克林顿基金会从 2003 年 12 月 31 日开始对财务报表进行了“明显有缺陷的审计”，并最终在美国境内外“虚假借口”筹集了数十亿美元。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “许多外国政府和许多富有的捐助者已经向克林顿基金会及其所谓的附属机构提供了数十亿美元的捐款，似乎没有注意到这些实体并没有正式存在或没有适当地报告他们的活动，”他继续说道。 “没有充分的理由证明这一已知的公共记录，也没有充分的理由相信捐助者寻求并可能从克林顿家族及其盟友那里获得的利益价值是他们对克林顿基金会捐款价值的许多倍。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110490817" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/durham-report-is-reckoning-coming-for-clintons-and-bidens-1110490817.html?share-block=1110491949" data-title="&quot;Many foreign governments and many rich contributors have sent, all together, billions of dollars in contributions towards the Clinton Foundation and its supposed affiliates without, seemingly, noticing that these entities did not formally exist or properly report concerning their activities,&quot; he continued. &quot;There is no good reason for this known public record and every reason to believe that donors sought and likely received benefits from the Clinton family and their allies worth many times the value of their contributions to the Clinton Foundation.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他怀疑奥巴马政府很清楚克林顿夫妇明显的违规行为，但为了将希拉里克林顿推上美国国务卿的位置而掩盖了这些行为。因此，按照奥特尔的说法，美国国税局、司法部和其他机构对克林顿基金会的“违规行为”视而不见。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">为什么特别顾问约翰·达勒姆 (John Durham) 不深入研究联邦当局对克林顿基金会案件的处理方式？ “最有可能的是，约翰·达勒姆 (John Durham) 无权追溯至 1997 年 10 月 23 日，”这位华尔街分析师推测道。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">克林顿夫妇和拜登夫妇对待儿童手套都一视同仁</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230207/bans-bucks--bureaucracy-twitter-files-co-author-taibbi-on-big-techs-collusion-with-feds-1107047111.html" target="_blank">埃隆·马斯克 (Elon Musk) 的 Twitter 文件</a>显示，美国联邦调查局 (FBI) 决定停止对强大的克林顿王朝家族展开调查，这似乎与美国情报界在 2020 年压制亨特·拜登 (Hunter Biden) “来自地狱的笔记本电脑”故事惊人地相似。此外，正如众议院议员最近透露的那样，多达<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20220526/if-hunters-laptop-from-hell-is-100-authentic-will-dirty-51-ex-spooks-be-held-accountable-1095806921.html" target="_blank">51 名前高级情报官员</a>迅速将《纽约邮报》投下的笔记本电脑重磅炸弹错误地贴上了“俄罗斯虚假信息”的标签，应当时的乔·拜登竞选活动特工安东尼·布林肯的要求。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">本月早些时候，众议院监督委员会主席詹姆斯·科默表示， <a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230511/fbi-refuses-republican-request-for-docs-tied-to-alleged-biden-criminal-scheme-1110250541.html" target="_blank">联邦调查局拒绝了众议院小组要求提供一份文件的请求</a>，该文件据称详细说明了<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230510/memo-biden-family-received-millions-from-foreigners-when-joe-was-vp-1110242908.html" target="_blank">乔·拜登总统参与</a>一项与外国人的非法计划。 “从联邦调查局的回应中可以清楚地看出，监督委员会传唤的非机密记录是存在的，但他们拒绝将其提供给委员会。我们已经要求联邦调查局不仅提供这份记录，还要告知我们它对我们做了什么调查这些指控。联邦调查局未能做到这两点，”科默在 5 月 10 日宣布。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> Ortel 说：“FBI 控制着颁发安全许可的过程，并且通过这个过程可能会了解很多关于联邦政府官员的信息。” “这项职能必须与其他调查活动完全分开，我怀疑它多年来一直没有分开。我们如何解释詹姆斯康梅在 2017 年 1 月 20 日之前吹嘘与当选总统特朗普对抗时表现出的神经？就职典礼和他从那时到现在的行为？如果联邦调查局在安全审查方面进展缓慢，那么它可能会阻碍即将上任的政府，就像特朗普政府所做的那样。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110490817" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/durham-report-is-reckoning-coming-for-clintons-and-bidens-1110490817.html?share-block=1110491950" data-title="&quot;The FBI controls the process of issuing security clearances and through this process likely learns much about many officials in the federal government,&quot; said Ortel. &quot;This function must be kept wholly separate from other investigative activities and I suspect it has not been kept separate for many years. How else do we explain the nerve exhibited by James Comey in bragging about confronting President-elect Trump before the January 20, 2017 Inauguration and his behavior from then to the present day? If the FBI slow-walks security reviews, it can then hobble the incoming administration, as it did in the case of the Trump administration.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="h3"><h3 class="article__h2">是时候调查深州腐败了</h3></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在达勒姆报告发布后，现任和前任美国立法者呼吁重新开始对克林顿基金会的调查。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">众议院司法委员会联邦政府武器化小组委员会成员、佛罗里达州共和党众议员马特·盖茨 (Matt Gaetz) 表示：“克林顿夫妇在联邦调查局有一组人对他们进行干预，以避免追究刑事责任。这些问题绝对值得进一步曝光和审查。”每日邮报。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “绝对应该重新审视这些调查。国会没有理由不能与追查克林顿基金会的现场特工举行一系列听证会，并对他们进行公开采访。这些问题绝对值得额外曝光和审查，”呼应前共和党国会议员和前众议院监督委员会主席贾森查菲茨。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110490817" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/durham-report-is-reckoning-coming-for-clintons-and-bidens-1110490817.html?share-block=1110491952" data-title="&quot;Absolutely these investigations should be revisited. There's no reason why Congress can't have a series of hearings with the field agents who were pursuing the Clinton Foundation, and public interviews with them as well. These matters absolutely warrant additional exposure and review,&quot; echoed former Republican congressman and ex-House Oversight Committee chair Jason Chaffetz."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Charles Ortel 表示希望达勒姆报告将引发“深入研究免税组织的活动，特别是当这些组织在国外运作和/或涉及政治家庭时。” </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “对所谓的免税组织的非法活动和腐败监督的真正调查应该是一个紧迫的、两党的优先事项，特别是在美国正在努力支付账单、减少我们的年度政府赤字和管理我们巨额债务的当下， ”华尔街分析师总结道。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110490817" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/durham-report-is-reckoning-coming-for-clintons-and-bidens-1110490817.html?share-block=1110491953" data-title="&quot;Real investigations of illegal activities and of corrupt oversight of supposed tax-exempt organizations should be an urgent, bi-partisan priority particularly in the present moment when America is struggling to pay its bills, reduce our annual government deficits and manage our towering debts,&quot; the Wall Street analyst concluded."></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 19:10:24 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/durham-report-is-reckoning-coming-for-clintons-and-bidens-1110490817.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/durham-report-is-reckoning-coming-for-clintons-and-bidens-1110490817.html<category>美洲</category><category>我们</category><category>希拉里·克林顿</category><category>比尔·克林顿</category><category>查尔斯奥特尔</category><category>联邦调查局</category><category>克林顿基金会</category><category>共和党人</category><category>达勒姆报告</category><category>约翰达勒姆</category><category>唐纳德·特朗普</category><category>亨特·拜登</category><category>中央情报局 (CIA)</category><category>笔记本电脑</category><category>付费玩</category><category>调查</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pledge of NATO Membership for Kiev Would Confirm Russia’s Warnings About Bloc’s Aggressive Posture]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110490624" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0c/10/1091567690_0:0:3076:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_17b4f2e147f9a6c4ac71b49ed160c08f.jpg?source-sid=" data-photoview-image-id="1091567686" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/pledge-of-nato-membership-for-kiev-would-confirm-russias-warnings-about-blocs-aggressive-posture-1110490624.html?share-img=1091567686"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sergei SUPINSKY</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2019 年 10 月 31 日，乌克兰总统泽伦斯基和北约秘书长延斯·斯托尔滕贝格在基辅会面后举行联合新闻发布会</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="" alt="Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky and NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg hold a joint press conference following a meeting in Kiev on October 31, 2019 - Sputnik International, 1920, 20.05.2023" title="2019 年 10 月 31 日，乌克兰总统泽伦斯基和北约秘书长延斯·斯托尔滕贝格在基辅会面后举行联合新闻发布会" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0c/10/1091567690_0:317:3076:2047_1920x0_80_0_0_b97764c87e048874ee353d3715cf0168.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0c/10/1091567690_0:317:3076:2047_640x0_80_0_0_f7fb1d367ab52b4a22c915784e41a911.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0c/10/1091567690_0:317:3076:2047_1280x0_80_0_0_c69661b3bde6f6290ff807f6493fd343.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/0c/10/1091567690_0:317:3076:2047_1920x0_80_0_0_b97764c87e048874ee353d3715cf0168.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 谢尔盖·苏宾斯基</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">伊利亚楚卡诺夫</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_tsukanov_ilya/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:i.tsukanov@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">自 2008 年在布加勒斯特举行的北约峰会以来，两个主要政党的美国官员一直在讨论乌克兰加入西方联盟的问题，这可能成为该军事集团数十年来积极向东扩张的顶点。这也是北约与俄罗斯在乌克兰进行代理人战争的主要原因之一。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在联盟即将举行的维尔纽斯峰会上给予基辅关于未来北约成员资格的任何形式的承诺将是一个糟糕的主意，这会破坏乌克兰的安全并导致莫斯科加倍开展其特别军事行动，大西洋理事会高级研究员约翰·R·德尼* ，总部位于华盛顿的顶级<a href="https://asiatimes.com/2022/06/neocon-think-tanks-are-driving-bidens-ukraine-policy/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">新保守主义</a>智囊团建议。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p>在最近为一家主要国际事务杂志<a href="https://foreignpolicy.com/2023/05/19/ukraine-nato-vilnius-zelensky-russia-summit/?tpcc=recirc_latest062921" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">发表的一篇专栏文章</a>中，同时也是美国陆军战争学院战略研究所教授的德尼警告说，“为乌克兰加入北约铺平道路”几乎肯定会“恶化乌克兰在短期”，延长和升级危机。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110490624" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/pledge-of-nato-membership-for-kiev-would-confirm-russias-warnings-about-blocs-aggressive-posture-1110490624.html?share-block=1110490626" data-title="In a recent op-ed for a major international affairs magazine, Deni, who is also a professor at the US Army War College’s Strategic Studies Institute, warned that ‘laying a path for Ukrainian membership in NATO’ would almost certainly “worsen Ukraine’s security in the short run,” prolonging and escalating the crisis."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这样做还会违反该联盟长期以来的成员规则——该规则要求候选国之间不存在未解决的内部冲突或与邻国的边界争端。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">德尼写道，加入成员国的承诺也将有助于“发挥”莫斯科关于该联盟利用乌克兰作为进一步侵略俄罗斯的起点的非常公开的警告，同时不诚实地将俄罗斯的这些担忧称为“普京的错误信息运动”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “让乌克兰走上更快、更清晰的加入北约的道路，将普京的宣传变成了预言，”这位观察员建议道，但没有详细说明北约两年半的扩张和<a href="https://mid.ru/ru/foreign_policy/rso/nato/1790818/?lang=en" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">俄罗斯拒绝两项全面的安全条约提案是如何</a>做到的于 2021 年底提出，这将有助于乌克兰保持中立，这构成了“宣传”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p>德尼表示，乌克兰在加入北约方面“在政治上还没有做好准备”，因为该国未能达到该联盟自称的自由民主标准，尤其是在过去一年观察到“对公民自由的镇压”之后。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110490624" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/pledge-of-nato-membership-for-kiev-would-confirm-russias-warnings-about-blocs-aggressive-posture-1110490624.html?share-block=1110490630" data-title="Ukraine is also “not ready politically” for NATO membership, according to Deni, with the country failing to meet the alliance’s self-proclaimed liberal democratic standards, particularly following the “crackdown on civil liberties” observed over the past year."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">北约不应向基辅提供如此正式的承诺，而应“关注盟友——尤其是欧洲盟友”如何“显着增加西方及其盟国先进军事平台的生产、交付和培训”，以对抗俄罗斯智库研究员认为，人力物力方面的优势。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">德尼的建议是新颖的，因为它来自华盛顿的顶级国际事务智囊团之一，其政策建议首先帮助引发了乌克兰危机。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国政界的反战声音提出了他们自己拒绝乌克兰加入北约的理由，理由包括危机<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230515/ukraines-fanatical-ex-envoy-to-germany-parachutes-into-brazil-to-wreak-havoc-1110385455.html" target="_blank">升级为全球热核战争的风险等。</a>本周在接受波兰媒体采访时，资深美国经济学家和公共政策分析师杰弗里萨克斯<a href="https://myslpolska.info/2023/05/19/jeffrey-sachs-usa-udaja-ze-rzadza-swiatem/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">表示</a>，华盛顿“傲慢”地拒绝考虑俄罗斯的国家安全利益和解决莫斯科对北约扩张的担忧是目前冲突的主要原因，其中乌克兰部队正在使用西方提供的武器与俄罗斯作战。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “俄罗斯永远不会接受乌克兰加入北约。它要么在战场上击败乌克兰，要么继续一场漫长而令人筋疲力尽的战争，”萨克斯警告说。 “总的来说，乌克兰加入北约没有现实的途径，”这位学者强调。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110490624" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230520/pledge-of-nato-membership-for-kiev-would-confirm-russias-warnings-about-blocs-aggressive-posture-1110490624.html?share-block=1110490635" data-title="“Russia will never accept Ukrainian membership in NATO. It will either defeat Ukraine on the battlefield or continue a long, exhausting war,” Sachs warned. “Overall, there is no realistic path to Ukraine’s membership in NATO,” the academic stressed."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">上周，著名国际关系学者约瑟夫·M·锡拉库扎博士<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230514/tallinn-security-conference-pours-gasoline-on-fire-of-russia-nato-proxy-war-in-ukraine-1110355015.html" target="_blank">告诉人造卫星网</a>，北约安全机构计划在不考虑俄罗斯利益的情况下继续扩大联盟。锡拉库萨说，当前的危机是由外交失败造成的，并且由于西方政策精英对基辅有能力打败俄罗斯的“错觉”期望而继续存在。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">从总统普京到外交部长谢尔盖拉夫罗夫的俄罗斯高级官员一再警告说，乌克兰加入北约是一条明亮的“红线”，俄罗斯永远不会接受被越过。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2021 年底，在俄罗斯的安全提案公布后，普京与华盛顿和布鲁塞尔进行了一系列来回的外交沟通，坦率地说，乌克兰的红线是他们没有任何战略回旋余地俄罗斯。北约将“在乌克兰部署导弹系统，飞行 4-5 分钟即可到达莫斯科……他们只是把我们逼到了这样一种状态，我们不得不告诉他们：停下来，”普京当时<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20211226/putin-on-red-lines-west-has-pinned-russia-into-a-position-where-it-has-nowhere-to-fall-back-to-1091813306.html" target="_blank">说</a>。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <em>* 被俄罗斯总检察长办公室列为不良实体。</em></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 20 May 2023 18:57:03 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/pledge-of-nato-membership-for-kiev-would-confirm-russias-warnings-about-blocs-aggressive-posture-1110490624.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230520/pledge-of-nato-membership-for-kiev-would-confirm-russias-warnings-about-blocs-aggressive-posture-1110490624.html<category>军队</category><category>弗拉基米尔普京</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>北约</category><category>大西洋理事会</category><category>我们</category><category>扩张</category><category>北约扩张</category></item></channel></rss>